labels.name: bug 🐛

issue.body:
### systemd version the issue has been seen with

257.6

### Used distribution

Nixos

### Linux kernel version used

6.16

### CPU architectures issue was seen on

x86_64

### Component

systemd-nspawn


### Unexpected behaviour you saw

When mounting a single file inside a symlink directory with idmap and privateUsers=pick, the container fail to start.

### Steps to reproduce the problem


mkdir /a/
touch /a/file
ln -s /a/ /b/
try to start the container with --bind(-ro or not)=/b/file:/b/file:idmap

### Additional program output to the terminal or log subsystem illustrating the issue

```sh
systemd-nspawn[54399]: Failed to map ids for bind mount /run/nixos-containers/.#machinename4719ff62fce7ecfc/a/single/file: Invalid argument
```

pull_request.title: feat: add branches and checkout commands
pull_request.body:
Add a 'g' group for git commands to the application, within this there are two new commands: branches, and co.

The branches command shows the branches available in the current repository, and optionally searches them. The search is very basic just checking for the search string within the branch name.

The co command uses the same logic as above, you can enter a branch name that you'd like to checkout and it will search branches for a match. If there is only one match, it will just check it out. If there are multiple matches, then it will present an interactive choice where you can use the TUI to select which branch you actually want.

To implement the choices TUI, I used the bubbletea package. This handles the interactivity for the app.

To implement the git commands, it is using the exec package, but i introduced a service within the hostsys package to abstract this a bit and avoid some duplication each time we need to call execute a tool in the system.

While doing this I also introduced a logging package that we can use to configure log levels throughout the app. As most of this is a kind of TUI, the errors are presented anyway so the log level by default is a custom "none" level that won't show anything. This log level is a persistent flag that can be changed on each command and will show more errors if needed for debugging.

**What this PR does / why we need it**:
The nightly build fails from time to time on unit tests, when trying to create dashboard handlers based on a non-exists directory of dashboard yamls.

The directory name is computed with:

dir := path.Join(os.TempDir(), fmt.Sprint(time.Now().UTC().Unix()))

This commit gives a unique directory name for each one of the tests that uses the temp directory name pattern, to ensure each test is using its own directory. Also, try to make these test more robust, by taking logic out of the `By` functions, and by adding some error checks.
